cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with problems related to packing and covering a polygon with geodesic disks, which are geometric optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves approximation algorithms, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of density and maximal radius in the algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
